{
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/main/sarif-2.1/schema/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "fullName": "Trivy Vulnerability Scanner",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy",
          "name": "Trivy",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "CVE-2022-40151",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "xstream: Xstream to serialise XML data was vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Those using Xstream to seralize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a denial of service attack."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-40151",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2022-40151\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream\nFixed Version: 1.4.20\nLink: [CVE-2022-40151](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-40151)\nThose using Xstream to seralize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a denial of service attack.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2022-40151**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream|1.4.20|[CVE-2022-40151](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-40151)|\n\nThose using Xstream to seralize XML data may be vulnerable to Denial of Service attacks (DOS). If the parser is running on user supplied input, an attacker may supply content that causes the parser to crash by stackoverflow. This effect may support a denial of service attack."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 7.5,
                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H",
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "HIGH"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2022-41966",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "xstream: Denial of Service by injecting recursive collections or maps based on element's hash values raising a stack overflow"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "XStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a denial of service only via manipulation the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation causing a stack overflow. This issue is patched in version 1.4.20 which handles the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of java.util.Map and java.util per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-41966",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2022-41966\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream\nFixed Version: 1.4.20\nLink: [CVE-2022-41966](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-41966)\nXStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a denial of service only via manipulation the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation causing a stack overflow. This issue is patched in version 1.4.20 which handles the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of java.util.Map and java.util per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2022-41966**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream|1.4.20|[CVE-2022-41966](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2022-41966)|\n\nXStream serializes Java objects to XML and back again. Versions prior to 1.4.20 may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error, resulting in a denial of service only via manipulation the processed input stream. The attack uses the hash code implementation for collections and maps to force recursive hash calculation causing a stack overflow. This issue is patched in version 1.4.20 which handles the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. A potential workaround for users who only use HashMap or HashSet and whose XML refers these only as default map or set, is to change the default implementation of java.util.Map and java.util per the code example in the referenced advisory. However, this implies that your application does not care about the implementation of the map and all elements are comparable."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 8.2,
                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:H",
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "8.2",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "HIGH"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-47072",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "com.thoughtworks.xstream: XStream is vulnerable to a Denial of Service attack due to stack overflow from a manipulated binary input stream"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the BinaryStreamDriver. XStream 1.4.21 has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the StackOverflowError in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the BinaryStreamDriver."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-47072",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-47072\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream\nFixed Version: 1.4.21\nLink: [CVE-2024-47072](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-47072)\nXStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the BinaryStreamDriver. XStream 1.4.21 has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the StackOverflowError in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the BinaryStreamDriver.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-47072**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|com.thoughtworks.xstream:xstream|1.4.21|[CVE-2024-47072](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-47072)|\n\nXStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. This vulnerability may allow a remote attacker to terminate the application with a stack overflow error resulting in a denial of service only by manipulating the processed input stream when XStream is configured to use the BinaryStreamDriver. XStream 1.4.21 has been patched to detect the manipulation in the binary input stream causing the the stack overflow and raises an InputManipulationException instead. Users are advised to upgrade. Users unable to upgrade may catch the StackOverflowError in the client code calling XStream if XStream is configured to use the BinaryStreamDriver."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 7.5,
                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H",
                "cvssv40_baseScore": 7.7,
                "cvssv40_vector": "CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:P",
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "7.5",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "HIGH"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2025-48976",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "apache-commons-fileupload: Apache Commons FileUpload DoS via part headers"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Allocation of resources for multipart headers with insufficient limits enabled a DoS vulnerability in Apache Commons FileUpload.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons FileUpload: from 1.0 before 1.6; from 2.0.0-M1 before 2.0.0-M4.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 1.6 or 2.0.0-M4, which fix the issue."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-48976",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-48976\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: commons-fileupload:commons-fileupload\nFixed Version: 1.6.0\nLink: [CVE-2025-48976](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-48976)\nAllocation of resources for multipart headers with insufficient limits enabled a DoS vulnerability in Apache Commons FileUpload.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons FileUpload: from 1.0 before 1.6; from 2.0.0-M1 before 2.0.0-M4.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 1.6 or 2.0.0-M4, which fix the issue.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-48976**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|commons-fileupload:commons-fileupload|1.6.0|[CVE-2025-48976](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-48976)|\n\nAllocation of resources for multipart headers with insufficient limits enabled a DoS vulnerability in Apache Commons FileUpload.\n\nThis issue affects Apache Commons FileUpload: from 1.0 before 1.6; from 2.0.0-M1 before 2.0.0-M4.\n\nUsers are recommended to upgrade to versions 1.6 or 2.0.0-M4, which fix the issue."
              },
              "properties": {
